column31: Bimi is really a very special vegetable. It is not found in nature because it is the result of a cross between two types of vegetables. You have probably already recognized one of these two varieties: broccoli. The other is a little less well-known, since kai-lan is mainly used as a leafy vegetable in Chinese cuisine. The result of this crossing is very tasty. Your palate will definitely recognize the broccoli. With the addition of the Kai-lan, the EAT ME-Bimi® even has a very fancy nickname: asparagus broccoli. In terms of taste, that's true. The vegetable has long, thin stems, so you can easily tell the difference to broccoli.
